<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Service (1995 through 1999) - SECTION 7: VIBRATION DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT, MAIN
        BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND CRANKCASE - CHECKING THE FLYWHEEL HOUSING
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>CHECKING THE FLYWHEEL HOUSING</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="check" graphiccount="0">
            <title>CHECKING FLYWHEEL HOUSING BORE CONCENTRICITY AND FACE RUNOUT</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Bore concentricity and face runout is checked to ensure proper engine to transmission
                        alignment.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>FAILURE TO INSURE PROPER BORE CONCENTRICITY AND FACE RUNOUT MAY RESULT IN REDUCED TRANSMISSION
                        LIFE.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check flywheel housing bore concentricity as follows. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e160_176.xml" xrefid="ef1600727">7.27</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    :
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Attach a dial indicator to the crankshaft and place the indicator tip against the
                        flywheel housing bore.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Zero the dial indicator.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Rotate the crankshaft slowly and record the total indicator variation. Refer to
                        <emph type="bold">SPECIFICATIONS</emph>
                        for tolerance.
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check flywheel housing face runout as follows. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e160_176.xml" xrefid="ef1600728">7.28</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    :
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Attach a dial indicator to crankshaft and place indicator tip against housing
                        face.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Measure at four points, 90&#176; apart for total face variation.</para>
                    <specpara>
                        <note>
                            <para>KEEP THE CRANKSHAFT END PLAY AT ZERO IN THE SAME DIRECTION FOR ALL MEASUREMENTS.
                            </para>
                        </note>
                    </specpara>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Refer to
                        <emph type="bold">SPECIFICATIONS</emph>
                        for housing face runout tolerance.
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
